     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Provide in secretariat and technical  support to NHRC&#x2019;s high-level network in monitoring human rights situation with reference to COVID 19. 
2. Develop human rights monitoring checklist  and  a Working Procedure 2020  guideline of the network to monitor human rights situation with reference to COVID 19.
3. Conduct psychosocial counseling and mental health training to conflict affected community  in Seven provinces.
4. 3 Crisis and disaster law reviewed from human rights perspective. 
5. Conduct monitoring of  the detention, old person shelters, correction centers in reference with Covid-19 by joint monitoring team.
6. Conduct study on human rights situation of vulnerable people 
7. Support in digitalization system to NHRC through developing apps and ICT for virtual meeting among concerned and hotline to receive the complaints.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. A total of 85 network in monitoring human rights situation with reference to COVID 19 comprised of 450  (Male: 350 Female 100) members were supported
2. Human rights PSA through local 34 FM stations in 14 local language broadcasted.
3. One human rights monitoring checklist  and  a Working Procedure 2020  guideline of the network to monitor human rights situation with reference to COVID 19 developed.
4. Conducted virtual psychosocial counseling and mental health training in Seven provinces for a total of 181 conflict affect victims including 110 women.  
5. 3 laws related to Infectious Disease,  Disaster Risk and Management Act and  Public Health Service Act reviewed from Social Security and Human Rights  Perspective.
6. 5 monitoring missions in regard with human rights situation in district, human rights situation of migrant workers, detainees people with disability conducted in 28 districts.
7. Conducted two studies on human rights situation of persons with disability and rights of migrant workers in clutches of covid-19 and recommended the government to intervene activities to ensure rights of these people.  
8. Human rights app developed and 10  virtual video conferencing system developed to replace paper-based complaint receiving into new innovation.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
